HEADWORD: Glandulation
<hw>Glan`du*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>glandulation</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The situation and
structure of the secretory vessels in plants.</def>
<rj><au>Martyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Glandulation</qex> respects the secretory vessels, which are
either glandules, follicles, or utricles.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Lee.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glandule</ent>⟦br⟧
